title: Updated Marker Plotting to Refer to CDN for Marker Images
body:
I updated the gmplot.py to refer to a github cdn, so that when the html map is created, it creates image without having to rely on the local machines file directory.

This is to:
1. Solve the issue where Marker images won't load on window machines.
2. Allow users to transfer their html maps to other users without a loss of markers.

title: Fixed gmplot.py import error : "from .color_dicts" to " from color_dicts"
body:
### Steps to reproduce
```
$ git clone https://github.com/vgm64/gmplot.git
$ python ./gmplot/gmplot.py
```

### Expected behavior

Produce mymap.html (./gmplot/)

### Actual behavior

Traceback (most recent call last):
File "gmplot.py", line 6, in 
from .color_dicts import mpl_color_map, html_color_codes
ValueError: Attempted relative import in non-package

### Codes to fix
```python
from .color_dicts import mpl_color_map, html_color_codes # before
from color_dicts import mpl_color_map, html_color_codes # after
```

### System configuration
python==2.7.11
gmplot==1.2.0

title: Text Labeling Support
body:
-added new marker, clear.png, 1x1 transparent pixel

-added text labelling support

gmap.text(lat,lng,color,text) will add to new self.text attribute

gmap.write_text iterates over text attribute, writes text in color
and location specified.  Utilizes clear.png marker so no marker is
shown, only text.

possible improvements: allow user to specify text size and alignment.

title: Include option to create satellite map by optional argument
body:
Enables choice between satellite map and road map creation by including map_type argument in GoogleMapPlotter:

1. Create a satellite map if 'satellite' is provided as map_type argument
`gmap = gmplot.GoogleMapPlotter(37.428, -122.145, 16, 'satellite')`

2. Create a road map if map_type argument is None or not 'satellite' 
`gmap = gmplot.GoogleMapPlotter(37.428, -122.145, 16)`
